 :tx/rationale "C9-COMPONENT-1: Observation corroboration detection — cluster independent observations by semantic similarity and detect convergence. PROBLEM: 4 independent audit agents produced 226 observations. Many describe the same finding (e.g., F(S) monotonicity falsified appears in all 4 reports). But the store treats each observation as independent — no mechanism detects that 4 sources agree on the same defect. Corroboration is the strongest epistemic signal: independent agreement is more certain than any single high-confidence observation. JUSTIFICATION: The concept engine (concept.rs) already performs agglomerative clustering over observation embeddings. It produces ConceptSummary with member counts and centroids. The missing step: after clustering, compute a corroboration score = number_of_distinct_agents_in_cluster / total_agents. A finding corroborated by 4/4 agents at confidence 0.85 is more certain than a single observation at 0.99. This is Bayesian: P(defect | 4 independent reports) >> P(defect | 1 report). SOLUTION: In concept.rs, after clustering, annotate each cluster with: (1) distinct agent sources (from :tx/agent on the observation's transaction), (2) corroboration score, (3) confidence range across members. Surface corroboration in seed assembly as a ranking signal. VERIFICATION: After running on the 226 audit observations, the top cluster should contain the F(S) monotonicity finding with corroboration=4/4. DEPENDENCIES: Uses existing concept engine. Feeds into C9-COMPONENT-3 (seed integration). FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs. EFFORT: 3h."
